properties.adviceB: Use diversions; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
Traffic management will be in place around University of Wollongong during morning peak periods to help ease congestion and queuing on the M1 Princes Motorway.

From 7:45am to 9:15am Monday to Friday:

  • M1 Princes Mwy southbound traffic exiting at University Ave will be diverted left to make a U-turn at the eastern roundabout.
  • Traffic at Irvine St will diverted left, to the University Western Access route.
  • Motorists wishing to access the M1 Princes Mwy northbound ramp (towards Sydney) at Northfields Ave will be diverted via Murphys Ave and Robsons Rd.

Motorists should allow extra travel time during morning peak and follow instructions of traffic controllers.
